ripts into a managed platform.\\n\\n### 1. What I Heard\\nYou want to build a React-based frontend for the ADK harness. This will serve as the primary interface for managing agents, viewing session history, and likely houses the **Managed Skill Registry** we planned earlier.\\n\\n### 2. Recommended Next Step\\nDraft the **APP_BRIEF.md** for the \\\"ADK Web Console.\\\" \\n\\nWe shouldn't write code until we define the \\\"Minimum Viable Console.\\\" Does it just do chat, or is it the command center for the entire factory? I recommend we start with a \\\"Chat + Session Viewer\\\" focus first.\\n\\n### 3. Options\\n*   **Option A: Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind + ShadCN**\\n    *   **Pros:** This is our standard high-fidelity stack. Provides the best DX for building the \\\"GHL-style\\\" skill management UI we want.\\n    *   **Cons:** Requires a Node.js environment and a clean API bridge to the existing Python ADK.\\n    *   **Pick:** **This is my recommendation.** It scales to the \\\"Platform\\\" vision.\\n*   **Option B: React + Vite (Single Page App)**\\n    *   **Pros:** Slightly lighter weight than Next.js if we don't need SSR.\\n    *   **Cons:** We\u2019ll eventually want the routing and API features of Next.js anyway.\\n\\n### 4. Risks / Red Flags\\n*   **The Auth Gap:** The current ADK harness has no authentication. A web frontend needs a secure way to talk to the backend without exposing your GCS buckets to the open web.\\n*   **Real-time Lag:** Agents are \\\"slow\\\" compared to standard web apps. The UI needs excellent \\\"Streaming/Thinking\\\" states to prevent it from feeling broken during long inference runs.\\n*   **State Conflict:** We need to ensure the React frontend isn't fighting with the GCS session memory for the \\\"source of truth.\\\"\\n\\n### 5. Action Checklist\\n1.  [ ] **Draft APP_BRIEF.md:** Define the specific screens (Chat, Skill Registry, Agent Config).\\n2.  [ ] **Define DATA_CONTRACT.md:** Map out the FastAPI endpoints the React app will consume.\\n3.  [ ] **Structure the Repo:** Decide if this lives in a `/web` folder in the current repo or a separate repository. (I recommend `/web` for a unified mono-repo approach).\\n\\n**Shall I start drafting the APP_BRIEF.md for the Web Console?**\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"intermediate_data\":{\"tool_uses\":[{\"id\":\"adk-ab8203fb-f4c0-49c0-aaa9-9372504ff4e3\",\"args\":{\"skill_name\":\"SESSION_MEMORY_SKILL\"},\"name\":\"invoke_skill\"},{\"id\":\"adk-9b9902e4-093b-4fbd-986d-ff01228c5f65\",\"args\":{\"days\":7},\"name\":\"read_session_memory\"}],\"intermediate_responses\":[]},\"creation_timestamp\":0.0},\"expected_invocation\":{\"invocation_id\":\"inv_scope_01\",\"user_content\":{\"parts\":[{\"video_metadata\":null,\"thought\":null,\"inline_data\":null,\"file_data\":null,\"thought_signature\":null,\"code_execution_result\":null,\"executable_code\":null,\"function_call\":null,\"function_response\":null,\"text\":\"Let's add a React frontend to this agent\"}],\"role\":\"user\"},\"final_response\":{\"parts\":[{\"video_metadata\":null,\"thought\":null,\"inline_data\":null,\"file_data\":null,\"thought_signature\":null,\"code_execution_result\":null,\"executable_code\":null,\"function_call\":null,\"function_response\":null,\"text\":\"\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"intermediate_data\":{\"tool_uses\":[],\"intermediate_responses\":[]},\"creation_timestamp\":0.0},\"eval_metric_results\":[{\"metric_name\":\"tool_trajectory_avg_score\",\"threshold\":1.0,\"judge_model_options\":null,\"score\":0.0,\"eval_status\":2},{\"metric_name\":\"response_match_score\",\"threshold\":0.7,\"judge_model_options\":null,\"score\":0.0,\"eval_status\":2}]}],\"session_id\":\"___eval___session___33a04cad-a9df-4fd5-bf62-ad81c49c717e\",\"session_details\":null,\"user_id\":\"test_user_id\"}],\"creation_timestamp\":1775223986.2491539}"